epi-FTD.def: Fish caught by trawling measures the percentage of a country’s fish caught by bottom trawling, where a fishing net is pulled along the seafloor behind a boat, or dredging, where the seafloor is scraped in search bottom-dwelling species. These practices are indiscriminate and wasteful and can severely damage marine ecosystems.
epi-FTD.name: Fish caught by Trawling and Dredging
